subSubSection.paragraph:
Cell II bearing 1–2(–3) perithecia or their initials, often on opposite sides. Above the cell II, 1–2 ± elongated cells bear upper corner cells in one side or on opposite sides giving rise to short branchlets bearing series of flask-shaped antheridia (
Fig. 54F
). Higher on the axis a similar cell forms the base of the appendage which consists of few to many variably elongated simple branches. [Detailed descriptions: 
Thaxter 1896
; Majewski & Sugiyama 1985; 
Santamaria 1989
; 
Majewski 1994b
]

On
Lathrobium brunnipes (Fabricius, 1792)
(Col. Staphylinidae Paederinae )
